Title

Data Cleaning Process

Content

Introduction

Before creating visualizations in Tableau, the heart disease dataset was checked to ensure that the data was clean, consistent, and ready for analysis.

Data Cleaning Steps

Imported the CSV dataset.
Checked all column names and data types.
Verified duplicate records.
Removed unnecessary spaces from text values.
Checked for invalid values in numerical columns.
Ensured categorical values such as sex, cp, and num were consistent.
Loaded the cleaned dataset into MySQL.

Outcome

The dataset was cleaned and prepared successfully for visualization and SQL analysis.